column5: Hit a stretch of Lac Seul tonight for a couple hours.  The spot is pretty close to town and it's a drive/walk out spot.  There's a small bridge over the road and therefore a current pinch.  Open water within 150 yards of where we were fishing.... on 2.5' of solid ice     Caught some walleye, including this nice fat female.  Full of eggs, released of course so she can spawn in another month.  Check out the blue tinge on her tail.

Ben did you get a measurement on her?  Man that is a beautiful eye and am not jealous at all LOL Good on ya for releasing her 2.5" of ice    don't you think that's cutting it a little thin?  Thanks for sharing and congratulations Jacques
Oooops me bad  Did you get a measurement on her??
I love/hate your reports. Nice walleye!
Beauty eye...  I miss not having those around.  I can't believe how deep blue her tail is.
Hey Jacques, I didn't measure her but I'm guessing she was an easy 5lbs.  I just wanted to get her and her eggs back in the lake
nice walleye Ben, sorry....i mean REALLY NICE walleye.  Cant wait to get up there in the boat in 6 weeks.....give that map you covered in Xs a go
way to rub it in. im not jelous or anything.
Nice eye Ben but you know you are breaking my heart here with all these updates and pics of fish up there I hope!
Ben, Don't have the boats out yet?  -s
thats a beauty eye Ben, i cant be jealous i still have a good solid 12inches of ice here. but no season!!!! keep them reports coming.  thanks for the read  Matt!
Not even close Sheldon!  I've gotta come back down south here soon to get in some soft-water action.
beauty eye!!!  30inches of ice still in april?  When does ice go out up there?  may long weekend?  Thanks for the report!  Cheers!
That's when it went out last year.  It can be gone by Mid april though, just depends on the winter.  This one, and last, were both long and cold.
